snippet.textDisplay:
Steve, the best thing for someone to do is to come forward with something that one person struggles with. Doing so only improves your look and just influences others to do so. I want to say that you are the best youtuber that I've known. I've watched so many of your videos, including your Talking Kitty Cat series, your 4Steves, and all of your music. Your music is very well written, and you inspire me. I used to have a cat, but I don't anymore. I tried to follow your guide on how to make a Talking Kitty video (Steve's 84th video) and it didn't work. I love watching Sylvester's villgalent attitude, Random's quirkiness, Gibbyson's randomness, GG's loving look, and Shelby's ability to continue, even though she can't do much about it. If I'm being honest, you are more like Shelby.


I still remember your old character, like the 4 Steves, Ibanez, Gibson, and the rest.. and I want you to know that people love you not for your look, but for who you are inside. And inside, you are a bundle of joy. And art of inspiration. You are very creative for being able to take cats, some of the most independent creatures on Earth, and turn them into loving animals. I want you to know that even if TKC ends, I will continue to support you and continue to watch your videos. You have made me very happy.
I want to share something with you as well.


I have ADHD. Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder. It's something that makes me not very good at directions. But I try not to reflect on that. Take it from me, a 15 y/o kid who doesn't really know much:
try not to reflect on the bad, and look at the good you do.




-A fan of you. Always.
Never give up, Steve.


Never give up.
